(6, 1, '2013-10-24 02:35:11', '2013-10-24 02:35:11', 'This is an example page. It''s different from a blog post because it will stay in one place and will show up in your site navigation (in most themes). Most people start with an About page that introduces them to potential site visitors. It might say something like this:\n\n<blockquote>Hi there! I''m a bike messenger by day, aspiring actor by night, and this is my blog. I live in Los Angeles, have a great dog named Jack, and I like pi&#241;a coladas. (And gettin'' caught in the rain.)</blockquote>\n\n...or something like this:\n\n<blockquote>The XYZ Doohickey Company was founded in 1971, and has been providing quality doohickeys to the public ever since. Located in Gotham City, XYZ employs over 2,000 people and does all kinds of awesome things for the Gotham community.</blockquote>\n\nAs a new WordPress user, you should go to <a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-admin/">your dashboard</a> to delete this page and create new pages for your content. Have fun!', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-10-24 02:35:11', '2013-10-24 02:35:11', '', 2, 'http://prana.gav.rtr/?p=6', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(7, 1, '2013-10-24 02:35:47', '2013-10-24 02:35:47', '<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_1277.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-63 alignleft" alt="IMG_1277" src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_1277.jpg" width="475" height="475" /></a>Welcome to our new website! Since launching Prana in October, we''ve already began to receive positive feedback from our current corporate clients:\r\n<blockquote>I am having a great week and I do attribute some of that to my breathing.  The staff absolutely love the yoga and I think it is making a huge difference.  We can’t thank you enough.</blockquote>\r\nWe''ve also been invited to speak at University of Western Ontario for the Introduction to Human Resource Management Continuing Studies Program, as well as to the Techalliance Women in Technology Peer to Peer group... and our client base continues to grow! Thank you to the London business community for being receptive and giving such a warm welcome to Prana.\r\n\r\nWe are also excited for our founder, Chantelle Diachina, who is currently in India to continue her yoga studies (<a href="http://diachinatravels.wordpress.com/">and for a little family traveling adventure!</a>) She looks forward to sharing what she has learned with our clients.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'What''s New', '', 'publish', 'open', 'closed', '', 'whats-new', '', '', '2013-11-10 01:51:05', '2013-11-10 01:51:05', '', 0, 'http://prana.gav.rtr/?page_id=7', 0, 'page', '', 0),
