(73, 2, '2013-11-09 19:02:17', '2013-11-09 19:02:17', '<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_1291.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-59 alignleft" alt="IMG_1291" src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_1291.jpg" width="359" height="359" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe specialize in corporate yoga and mental wellness in the workplace.\r\n\r\nWithin our society we continue to observe stress levels steadily increasing and our health and happiness steadily decreasing. The Prana team feels it is time to take the famed Eastern approach to mindfulness, positive psychology and self-care and make it practical and accessible to everyone.\r\n\r\nWe currently offer on-site yoga classes in corporate spaces and privately in client homes. We also offer "off-the-mat" professional development seminars, workshops and team retreats focused on self-care and building resiliency to stress.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1>Meet Our Team</h1>\r\n<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_2018.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-71 " alt="Laura Johnson R.Y.T." src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_2018-300x300.jpg" width="300" height="300" /></a>\r\n\r\nLAURA JOHNSON\r\nREGISTERED YOGA TEACHER\r\n\r\nLaura came to yoga because she thought it would make her stronger during a time when her body was weak– and it did, but it didn’t stop there. Over time she realized yoga was also making her a better human.\r\n\r\nLaura went on to received her 200 hr Yoga Teacher Training from The Lotus Centre in London, Ontario in 2010.   She continues to strive to live and breathe yoga each moment through the good times and bad times, while holding on to the teachings that have moulded her thus far, which keeping her grounded, balanced and happy. Laura is registered with the Canadian Yoga Alliance. You can also catch a class with Laura at Karma Yoga Studio and at her private home studio.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_2019.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-72 alignleft" title="Kim Ellig-Picken" alt="IMG_2019" src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_2019-300x300.jpg" width="300" height="300" /></a>KIM ELLIG-PICKEN\r\nREGISTERED YOGA TEACHER\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-09 19:02:17', '2013-11-09 19:02:17', '', 2, 'http://prana.gav.rtr/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(74, 2, '2013-11-09 19:03:23', '2013-11-09 19:03:23', '<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_1291.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-59 alignleft" alt="IMG_1291" src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_1291.jpg" width="359" height="359" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe specialize in corporate yoga and mental wellness in the workplace.\r\n\r\nWithin our society we continue to observe stress levels steadily increasing and our health and happiness steadily decreasing. The Prana team feels it is time to take the famed Eastern approach to mindfulness, positive psychology and self-care and make it practical and accessible to everyone.\r\n\r\nWe currently offer on-site yoga classes in corporate spaces and privately in client homes. We also offer "off-the-mat" professional development seminars, workshops and team retreats focused on self-care and building resiliency to stress.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1>Meet Our Team</h1>\r\n<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_2018.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-71 alignleft" alt="Laura Johnson R.Y.T." src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_2018-300x300.jpg" width="300" height="300" /></a>\r\n\r\nLAURA JOHNSON\r\nREGISTERED YOGA TEACHER\r\n\r\nLaura came to yoga because she thought it would make her stronger during a time when her body was weak– and it did, but it didn’t stop there. Over time she realized yoga was also making her a better human.\r\n\r\nLaura went on to received her 200 hr Yoga Teacher Training from The Lotus Centre in London, Ontario in 2010.   She continues to strive to live and breathe yoga each moment through the good times and bad times, while holding on to the teachings that have moulded her thus far, which keeping her grounded, balanced and happy. Laura is registered with the Canadian Yoga Alliance. You can also catch a class with Laura at Karma Yoga Studio and at her private home studio.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_2019.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-72 alignleft" title="Kim Ellig-Picken" alt="IMG_2019" src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_2019-300x300.jpg" width="300" height="300" /></a>KIM ELLIG-PICKEN\r\nREGISTERED YOGA TEACHER\r\n\r\n&nbsp;', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-09 19:03:23', '2013-11-09 19:03:23', '', 2, 'http://prana.gav.rtr/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
