much more.\r\nAs a survivor of domestic violence, Chantelle experienced first hand the incredible healing power yoga has on the mind, body and soul. She also noticed she was sick with colds and flu less often and was better prepared to face the stresses of day to day life.\r\n\r\nAfter more than a decade of being a classroom teacher, Chantelle left her career to pursue her passion for yoga. In 2007, she traveled to Miramar, Florida to study under Master Yogi Hari Sukhu of the Sivananda lineage and receive her 200-hour yoga teacher certification. Not sure if she made the right choice, Chantelle continued to teach a few yoga classes, but returned to school a year later and received her certification in Public Relations and Communications from Fanshawe College. She was immediately hired upon graduation with digital agency, rtraction, as their client relations manager, but it only took a few years before the yoga called her back. From colleagues asking her for advice on personal life issues and ways to loosen tense muscles to being invited to speak about workplace wellness for a Regional Mental Health Care Lunch and Learn at St. Joeseph''s Hospital, Chantelle realized there was a high need for yoga and effective stress management in the workplace. In January of 2013, Chantelle left rtraction and began to pour her heart and soul into creating Prana Yoga &amp; Wellness, which officially launched in October 2013.\r\n\r\nChantelle also offers classes through Forest City Sport &amp; Social Club, Downtown Yoga Holistic Centre and at her private home studio.', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-09 21:00:00', '2013-11-09 21:00:00', '', 2, 'http://prana.gav.rtr/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(85, 2, '2013-11-09 21:01:58', '2013-11-09 21:01:58', '<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_1291.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-59 alignleft" alt="IMG_1291" src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_1291.jpg" width="359" height="359" /></a>\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\nWe specialize in corporate yoga and mental wellness in the workplace.\r\n\r\nWithin our society we continue to observe stress levels steadily increasing and our health and happiness steadily decreasing. The Prana team feels it is time to take the famed Eastern approach to mindfulness, positive psychology and self-care and make it practical and accessible to everyone.\r\n\r\nWe currently offer on-site yoga classes in corporate spaces and privately in client homes. We also offer "off-the-mat" professional development seminars, workshops and team retreats focused on self-care and building resiliency to stress. All of our teachers are registered with the Yoga Alliance and/or Canadian Yoga Alliance and are fully insured.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n<h1>Meet Our Team</h1>\r\n<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_2018.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-71 alignleft" alt="Laura Johnson R.Y.T." src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_2018-300x300.jpg" width="300" height="300" /></a><strong>\r\nLAURA JOHNSON</strong>\r\n<strong> REGISTERED YOGA TEACHER</strong>\r\n\r\nLaura came to yoga because she thought it would make her stronger during a time when her body was weak– and it did, but it didn’t stop there. Over time she realized yoga was also making her a better human.\r\n\r\nLaura went on to received her 200 hr Yoga Teacher Training from The Lotus Centre in London, ON in 2010.  She continues to strive to live and breathe yoga each moment through the good times and bad times, while holding on to the teachings that have molded her thus far, which keeping her grounded, balanced and happy. Laura is registered with the Canadian Yoga Alliance. You can also catch a class with Laura at Karma Yoga Studio and at her private home studio.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_2019.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-72 alignleft" title="Kim Ellig-Picken" alt="IMG_2019" src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_2019-300x300.jpg" width="300" height="300" /></a><strong>\r\nKIM ELLIG-PICKEN</strong> B. Ed\r\n<strong> REGISTERED YOGA TEACHER\r\n</strong>\r\n\r\nAfter a few yoga classes at a local community centre, Kim knew she had finally found a fun, physical activity that was easy on her joints, alleviated anxiety, and helped her learn how to relax!\r\n\r\nAlso an educator, Kim has spent most of her career as a Learning Support Teacher, specializing in supporting students and families in trauma and/or struggling with social-emotional and mental health issues. Soon Kim''s passions for teaching, yoga, and promoting and improving physical and mental health began to evolve into a career beyond the educational system. In 2012, Kim received her 200 hr Yoga Teacher certification from Maha Pura Yoga Studio in Guelph, ON. You can also take classes with Kim in Strathroy and Parkhill through her yoga business, Mother Nurture Yoga &amp; Wellness, offering Interdisciplinary Hatha Yoga classes in Strathroy and Parkhill.\r\n\r\n&nbsp;\r\n\r\n<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Prana-pic.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-81 alignleft" title="Chantelle Diachina, E-RYT &amp; Founder of Prana" alt="Prana pic" src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Prana-pic.jpg" width="290" height="434" /></a>\r\n<strong>CHANTELLE DIACHINA</strong> B.Ed, M.Ed<strong> E-RYT &amp; FOUNDER of PRANA</strong>\r\n\r\nYoga came into Chantelle''s life in 2001, while living in Brampton, ON. Her first yoga teacher was Kiran, who was from India and had been taught yoga as a child by her grandfather. What Chantelle thought was just another form of exercise, quickly became so much more.\r\nAs a survivor of domestic violence, Chantelle experienced first hand the incredible healing power yoga has on the mind, body and soul. She also noticed she was sick with colds and flu less often and was better prepared to face the stresses of day to day life.\r\n\r\nAfter more than a decade of being a classroom teacher, Chantelle left her career to pursue her passion for yoga. In 2007, she traveled to Miramar, Florida to study under Master Yogi Hari Sukhu of the Sivananda lineage and receive her 200-hour yoga teacher certification. Not sure if she made the right choice, Chantelle continued to teach a few yoga classes, but returned to school a year later and received her certification in Public Relations and Communications from Fanshawe College. She was immediately hired upon graduation with digital agency, rtraction, as their client relations manager, but it only took a few years before the yoga called her back. From colleagues asking her for advice on personal life issues and ways to loosen tense muscles to being invited to speak about workplace wellness for a Regional Mental Health Care Lunch and Learn at St. Joeseph''s Hospital, Chantelle realized there was a high need for yoga and effective stress management in the workplace. In January of 2013, Chantelle left rtraction and began to pour her heart and soul into creating Prana Yoga &amp; Wellness, which officially launched in October 2013.\r\n\r\nChantelle also offers classes through Forest City Sport &amp; Social Club, Downtown Yoga Holistic Centre and at her private home studio.', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-09 21:01:58', '2013-11-09 21:01:58', '', 2, 'http://prana.gav.rtr/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
