(97, 2, '2013-11-19 17:43:09', '2013-11-19 17:43:09', '<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_1277.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-63 alignleft" alt="IMG_1277" src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/IMG_1277.jpg" width="475" height="475" /></a>Welcome to our new website! Since launching Prana in October, we''ve already began to receive positive feedback from our current corporate clients:\n<blockquote>I am having a great week and I do attribute some of that to my breathing.  The staff absolutely love the yoga and I think it is making a huge difference.  We can’t thank you enough.</blockquote>\nWe''ve also been invited to speak at University of Western Ontario for the Introduction to Human Resource Management Continuing Studies Program, as well as to the Techalliance Women in Technology Peer to Peer group... and our client base continues to grow! Thank you to the London business community for being receptive and giving such a warm welcome to Prana.\n\nWe are also excited for our founder, Chantelle Diachina, who is currently in India to continue her yoga studies and expand on her personal practice (<a href="http://diachinatravels.wordpress.com/">and for a little family traveling adventure!</a>) She looks forward to sharing what she has learned with our clients.\n\n&nbsp;', 'What''s New', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '7-autosave-v1', '', '', '2013-11-19 17:43:09', '2013-11-19 17:43:09', '', 7, 'http://prana.gav.rtr/7-autosave-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
(100, 2, '2013-11-09 21:34:44', '2013-11-09 21:34:44', 'In the last decade, much attention has been paid to increasing physical activity and supporting healthy eating in the workplace. These are good places to start, however when it comes to true wellness, Prana believes emotional and mental fitness also plays an important role. The World Health Organization (WHO) agrees. They have defined positive mental health as “a state of well-being in which every individual realizes his or her potential, can cope with normal stresses of life, can work productively and fruitfully and is able to make a contribution to his or her community. In the workplace there can be no health without mental health.”\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>WHY IT''S IMPORTANT</strong>\r\n\r\nIn January of 2013, The Canadian Standards Association (CSA) Group released the new National Standard of Canada on Psychological Health and Safety in the Workplace in response to some compelling statistics on how chronic stress, anxiety and depression are affecting working Canadians. It is estimated that Canada spends $51-billion per year on absenteeism, productivity, indemnities and healthcare as a result of mental health disorders. These new standards will play an important role to employers wishing to achieve the rank of “top employer” and implement best practices.\r\n\r\nBy implementing an approach to workplace wellness that targets stress management and overall well-being, organizations can more effectively:\r\n\r\n•    recruit and retain employees\r\n•    increase productivity and profit\r\n•    reduce costs related to employee sick leave, health plan expenses and workers''\r\ncompensation and disability claims\r\n•    build a stronger team and boost morale\r\n•    control costs due to employee absenteeism and “presenteeism”*\r\n\r\n*presenteeism is a term to describe employees who are physically at work, but due to stress are highly distracted and mentally preoccupied, which greatly affects productivity.\r\n\r\n\r\n<strong>WHAT WE OFFER</strong>\r\n\r\nWhile there is no magic pill or quick fix, The Prana team has tools to offer that when practiced over time, will help your employees build resilience to stress, thereby promoting and protecting your team’s well being.\r\n\r\nWe offer both "on-the-mat" and "off-the-mat" services at your place of work: yoga and mindfulness classes, seminars, workshops, retreats related to work-life balance, mental-emotional wellness, stress management and self-care.\r\n\r\nFor any wellness program to be successful, it is important the employees see the value in it, which is why we believe all members of the organization should be part of the collaboration process to discover the perfect combination of services for your team.  Contact us today for a consultation.', 'Workplace Wellness', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '9-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-09 21:34:44', '2013-11-09 21:34:44', '', 9, 'http://prana.gav.rtr/9-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
