tions from Fanshawe College. She was immediately hired upon graduation with digital agency, rtraction, as their client relations manager, but it only took a few years before the yoga called her back. From colleagues asking her for advice on personal life issues, how to loosen tense muscles to being requested to teach private group classes and speaking about workplace wellness for a Regional Mental Health Care Lunch and Learn at St. Joseph''s Hospital, Chantelle realized there was a high need for yoga and effective stress management in the workplace. In January of 2013, Chantelle left rtraction and began to pour her heart and soul into creating Prana Yoga &amp; Wellness, which officially launched in October 2013 and she hasn''t looked back since. Chantelle is registered as an experienced yoga teacher with <a href="http://yogaalliance.org/">Yoga Alliance.</a>\r\n\r\nChantelle also offers classes through <a href="fcssc.ca/register/more/5">Forest City Sport &amp; Social Club</a>, <a href="http://www.downtownlondonyoga.ca/Calendarbyteacher.aspx">Downtown Yoga Holistic Centre </a>and at her private home studio.\r\n\r\nTwitter: <a href="https://twitter.com/paisley_girl73">@paisley_girl73</a>\r\nBlog: <a href="http://www.neverwateraweed.blogspot.ca/">neverwateraweed.blogspot.ca</a>', 'About', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '2-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-18 15:40:34', '2013-11-18 15:40:34', '', 2, 'http://prana.gav.rtr/2-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
