(193, 2, '2013-11-19 17:34:40', '2013-11-19 17:34:40', 'Many of us have been conditioned to keep work and personal life separate and have been failing miserably. Now we are convinced if we just achieve work/life balance we would be better off. The problem is we are still separating the two. Let me make this clear: There is no such thing as work/life balance. There is however, "life balance".\r\n\r\nLife balance entails an understanding that your life has a beginning, which we''ll call "Point A" and it has an ending, which we''ll call "Point B". Everything in between these two points is your life; work included. To have life balance has everything to do with how you move between point A and B and nothing to do with taking minutes and hours from this basket over here and putting more minutes and hours in that basket over there. The latter is way too stressful– trust me, I know!\r\n\r\nNo... Life balance begins with you. It begins with committing to take care of yourself, to learn how to breathe, sleep, eat and move better. It''s desiring to have a good quality of life as you approach Point B, which begins now. It will involve stripping away some unnecessary things in your life: be they excessive, counterproductive to your well-being or clearly a waste of your precious time.\r\n\r\nThis is your life and as an adult, you are it''s one and only custodian. Stop wasting time worrying about how to do it all. Instead, start making some tough calls (a.k.a. sacrifices) and practicing mindful self-care.  The rest will follow.\r\n\r\n<a href="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Chantelle-Twitter-Pic-3.jpg"><img class="size-medium wp-image-80 alignleft" alt="Chantelle Diachina" src="http://prana.gav.rtr/wp-content/uploads/2013/01/Chantelle-Twitter-Pic-3-200x300.jpg" width="117" height="176" /></a>\r\n<em>Chantelle is the founder of Prana Yoga &amp; Wellness. She does the necessary work to remain happily married and to be a positive role model to her two school age daughters. Things you may not know about Chantelle: she once was lost in Thailand but was saved by a random motorcyclist from California; hearing her children fight irritates her to no end (does lack of sleep); she once showed up to a potluck party on the wrong night– she brought her dish to share, though!</em>', 'Work/Life Balance?', '', 'inherit', 'open', 'open', '', '43-revision-v1', '', '', '2013-11-19 17:34:40', '2013-11-19 17:34:40', '', 43, 'http://prana.gav.rtr/43-revision-v1/', 0, 'revision', '', 0),
